<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5812Anti-War/9: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-01T17:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            1, 1928—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September
                                    1—3:00 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>17. Department’s circular of August 16, 11 p.m. In a note dated today
                                Minister for Foreign Affairs acknowledged the receipt of my note of
                                August 27, containing the text of the Multilateral Anti-War Treaty
                                and replies as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Animated by the same desire to ensure the maintenance of
                                        peace which inspired the signatory powers, the Royal
                                        Government proposes to ask the Riksdag as soon as possible
                                        to give its consent to Sweden’s adherence to the
                                        [above-mentioned] treaty.”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <p>A statement to this effect will be given out tonight and full text
                                will be released on September 3.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>